Interpreting the Salt name as a faded white tone, with a hint of green in some areas, similar to the Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock colourway. The upper on this new Yeezy Salt 700 Boost is dipped entirely in the subtle look and rests atop an all-white midsole. The outsole comes in black to provide some contrast to the shoe, along with a singular black hit on the heel of the sole. This Adidas Yeezy 700 Salt is clean, crisp and unquestionable stylish, can't help but see shades of a classic workout Reebok when I look at this creation but by no means is this shoe an imitation. The Yeezy 700 Salt is right on trend with the dad shoe culture, and this colourway is a great extension of that movement and is sure to sell out everywhere quickly.

fields.name: Yeezy 350 V2 Yeezreel Nr

data.description: The Yeezy Boost 350 v2 Yeezreel arrives alongside two equally striking colourways just in time for Christmas 2019. Aesthetically similar to the Yeezy Boost 350 Glow, this ultra vibrant iteration features a striking green Primeknit upper, that is contrasted with an extremely unique black pattern that is layered into every inch of this design. Green speckled rope laces tie the shoe together while a vibrant midsole is deployed in a slightly translucent makeup to showcase the boost technology within.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016)

data.description: After the success of the OG Pirate colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016) makes a return a year on. Its breathable knitted upper takes on a subtle marble pattern and is finished with a handy pull tab at the heel. The integrated lace closure allows for a secure fit, while Boost cushioning in the midsole offers comfort. Complete with a rubber outsole underfoot, the Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016) is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite

data.description: First surfacing in 2020, the Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite takes inspiration from the original Wave Runner. Crafted from breathable Primeknit, the sock-like upper hosts caging detail, a secure lace-up fastening and minimalistic branding. Underfoot, Boost cushioning delivers all-day support. Buy and sell the Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx

data.description: In-keeping with Kanye West's minimalistic style, the Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx delivers a comfortable sneaker with a futuristic silhouette. Crafted with a flexible Primeknit upper, underfoot cushioning provides all-day comfort, balanced by a functional lacing system. Buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 V3 Fade Carbon

data.description: There’s no doubt that Kanye’s Yeezy range has it covered when it comes to striking colourways and eye-catching design, and this offering in Fade Carbon is no different. The Yeezy 700 V3 Fade Carbon is the latest colourway in the Yeezy range, offering a bright futuristic look with the textured caging design on the premium upper. The shoe embraces a striped monofilament with a mesh base, with a bold pink and purple gradient hue across the top. The bold colours are complemented by deep black accents on top. The upper comes with the Yeezy sock comfort you’d expect, while the sole swaps the Boost unit for an EVA foam comfort option. With the striking colourway and the cushioned layered look, this is certainly one for the courts or for the streets to get people talking.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe

data.description: Dressed in a neutral beige colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe will instantly elevate any of your everyday looks. Its patchwork-style Primeknit upper is complete with a mesh stripe and an integrated lacing system. Underfoot, the Boost midsole delivers comfort and the textured rubber outsole provides effective grip. Finished with minimal branding, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 380 Mist Nr

data.description: Playfully dubbed the mouldy bread, the Yeezy 380 Mist might be mistaken for being a less serious member of the Yeezy catalogue, but despite its sense of humour about itself the Mist is definitely no joke when it comes to its design and application. Mixing a palette of olive, brown and tan across the shoes spotted knit upper, the Yeezy Boost 380 Mist is visually unique from previous colourways from the brand, and its shape is one of the more original in Kanye West's portfolio. Shedding the 350s signature ribbed armour in favour of a smooth finish on the rubber that covers the embedded Boost cushioning. The jury is out on whether or not this silhouette will reach the same heights as the Yeezy Boost 350, but the Yeezy 380 Mist Boost for one is certainly making its case loud and clear.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin

data.description: Dropping on the most up to date variation on the Yeezy Boost 350 v2 silhouette, which arrives minus the heel pull tab. The Yeezy Citrin colourway stitches together muted yellow and brownish Primeknit elements across the entirety of the shoes upper. Translucent monofilament panels are inserted into the sides of the Citrin Yeezy, a staple of the v2 model, while Its distinctive TPU ribbed rubber sole, encasing Boost cushioning, is updated with a contrast tread pattern. The Yeezy 350 Citrin design is the manifestation of Kanye West's unique design methodology and cultural influence and arriving September 2019 is another great example of that.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Semi Frozen Yellow

data.description: First hitting stores in November 2017, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Semi Frozen Yellow thanks to numerous leaks across Instagram and Twitter was unveiled several months before anything was confirmed by Kanye and Adidas, but this only helped the release gather hype like a freight train through 2017. The Semi Frozen Yellows bright neon colourway is sure to cause a splash in the last few months of 2017 heading into 2018, arguably the most controversial ‘SPLY-V2' yet and said to be the most limited. Whether you are a fan or a critique Kanye very much takes the stance that all publicity is good publicity, and you can't argue everyone is taking notice. Drawing similarities with the much acclaimed ‘Zebra' colourway think of the Semi Frozen Yellow as the Zebra on acid. The highlighter yellow is really the star of the show, but this shoe is still adorned with all the classic Yeezy 350 trimming you would expect from an item coming out of this continuingly groundbreaking and modern portfolio.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah

data.description: Using Kanye West’s famous silhouette from collaborative Yeezy range, the Yeezy 700 v3 Alvah combines black and grey mesh for a minimalistic look. Built with RPU overlays, the grey mesh base offers breathability. Reflective accents update the tongue and the EVA midsole provides cushioning. Buy and sell the Yeezy 700 v3 Alvah with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Non-Reflective

data.description: Built with comfort and cost-effective construction in mind, the Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Non-Reflective takes on an earthy colourway. Boasting a Primeknit upper with breathable perforations, rope-like laces and the sock-like collar provide all-day support. Complete with Boost cushioning underfoot, the Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Non-Reflective is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Reflective

data.description: Dropped exclusive in December 2018 on the Yeezy Supply website, the Yeezy 350 V2 Static Reflective Boost is an ultra limited release featuring the same look as to be expected from the ‘Static' colourway but also featuring reflective accents in the Primeknit yarns. Drawing many parallels with Kanye West's close friend and Off-White designer Virgil Abloh, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Reflective is quite possibly the most unusual design in the Yeezy range. A bold leap from the conventional ‘SLPY-350' the Static Reflective Yeezy now showcases an industrial-inspired upper, utilising an array of deconstructed features more akin to the Off-White Nike range than Yeezy products of the past. This slick shoe's stylings which we have all come to expect from Kanye West's designs has refreshingly been given a unique new detailing for the last month of 2018, going into the New Year. The Yeezy 350 Static is unlike any previous release we have seen, and it is becoming more and more evident that although existing in direct competition with one another, both Kanye West's Yeezy and Virgil Abloh's Off-White ranges, might quite possibly be cross-pollinating. Be ready for 2019, because it's only getting better with the Yeezy Static Reflective

fields.name: Yeezy 500 Enflame

data.description: Boasting a mismatched colourway, the Yeezy 500 Enflame presents a unique iteration of the futuristic 500 model. Its breathable mesh base is decorated with suede overlays and leather tongue detailing. Subtle branding features on the adiPrene midsole which offers comfort and the rubber outsole provides grip. Finished with padding in the collar, the Yeezy 500 Enflame is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Non-Reflective

data.description: Crafted from one piece of durable PrimeKnit, the Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Non-Reflective is a seamless design from the adidas x Kanye West partnership. Breathable perforations deliver enhanced ventilation, while Boost cushioning and a thick midsole work to optimise performance and comfort. A colourful camouflage print ensures versatile styling potential and minimalist branding adds a sophisticated edge. Buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Non-Reflective with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite

data.description: The wait is over for another Yeezy to release, with the upcoming Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite guaranteed to excite fans of this iconic collaboration. Perhaps the most eye-catching colourway of the 380 so far, this sneaker is an absolute must-cop. The upper comes crafted from primeknit material, which we know guarantees unbeatable comfort. Kanye West has swapped out his usual earth tone colour palette for a mix of blues this time around, with deep navy laces also featuring. Down below, a sleek gum sole unit perfectly contrasts the various shades of blue used for the upper of the shoe. This sole unit houses the legendary Ultra Boost technology, guaranteeing comfort wear after wear. The Covellite is the perfect silhouette for the summer months, be sure to add a pair to your rotation today.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Inertia

data.description: Doused in an ultra clean grey hue with light orange accents throughout for a pop of contrast the Yeezy 700 Inertia released in March 2019 to me is one of Kanye West's most aesthetically pleasing designs. The Yeezy Inertia is finely crafted from luxe suede, premium leather, and breathable mesh and rested atop a boost infused midsole which has now become iconic with the prevalent and slightly confusing dad shoe movement and combines it with a robust and durable gum rubber outsole underneath. The Yeezy Boost 700 Inertia builds on the success of previous 700 models and creates a colourway which is muted but still very memorable, the bluish grey complexion the shoe boasts is one of Yeezy catalogues more delicate, and the peachy orange flecks really do finish this design excellently. The Yeezy 700 v2 Inertia is going to go toe to toe with 2019's best trainers, and you should look to get your hands on a pair as a matter of urgency.

fields.name: Yeezy 450 Stone Grey

data.description: Boasting a muted monochrome colourway, the Yeezy 450 Stone Grey also takes on futuristic aesthetics and minimal branding. Its breathable Primeknit base features a unique teeth-like caging system which offers added support. Underfoot, classic cushioning delivers all-day comfort and the rubber outsole provides grip. Fastened with an integrated lacing system, add the Yeezy 450 Stone Grey to your collection now.

fields.name: Yeezy Slides Resin 2021

data.description: A shoe that divided opinion when it first landed in 2019, the adidas x Yeezy Slide has since become a certified staple. Arriving in a versatile neutral colourway, the Yeezy Slides Resin 2021 is crafted from Earth-conscious EVA foam with a contoured footbed and serrated tread for grip. Branding is kept to a minimum with simple adidas stripes present on the insole. Buy and sell the Yeezy Slides Resin 2021 with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 Stone

data.description: First seen in 2019, the Yeezy 500 Stone presents a neutral take on the iconic silhouette. Crafted with a neoprene upper for a smoother aesthetic, it’s surrounded by premium suede overlays on the heel, sidewall and toe cap. Leather adorns the supportive mudguard, set atop a adiPrene-cushioned midsole. Topped with functional laces, buy and sell the Yeezy 500 Stone with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Qntm Frozen Blue

data.description: One of the wildest releases we have seen from Kanye West and Adidas sees a new colourway drop this week, the Frozen Blue version of the Yeezy QNTM. A sneaker meant to be the first Yeezy silhouette to grace the NBA has instead found success within the sneaker community. We see the iconic primeknit material used for the sneakers upper, whilst suede graces the shoe's toebox. Intricate detailing runs across the entire upper of the sneaker, perfectly mixing whites and frozen blue hues throughout. The ankle support comes crafted from neoprene to offer unparalleled support and comfort. The upper also has a glow in the dark effect, making this basketball sneaker one of a kind. Underfoot, we are treated to a full-length Yeezy ultra boost unit housed within a sleek, translucent sole unit. The sneaker will see two iterations release, a lifestyle pair and a court specific release. Don't miss out on the chance to own this legendary Yeezy.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Mnvn Bright Cyan

data.description: Yeezy’s fascinating silhouette and popular Boost technology ditches any previous neutral offerings and replaces them with a bright blue shade you’ll want to get your hands on. The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan is a shoe that’s set to catch anyone’s attention and a colour palette you can show off no matter where you go. The comfortable nylon upper is where you can see the bright cyan in all its glory. This is complemented by silver and black offerings on the rest of the shoe. These silver accents are also reflective, a feature many Yeezy fans will be used to. The classic Yeezy lacing system remains with black laces, working perfectly against the cyan upper. The chunky mid and outer sole keeps its focus on cushioned technology, supportive fit, and versatility, making the Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan an all-round must-have.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static Infants

data.description: Give your little one a stylish start by treating them to the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static Infants. The white and grey colourway adds more versatility to your growing child's wardrobe, as the neutral shades can complement a range of clothing styles in their wardrobe. Also, the Yeezy Boost technology provides soft, responsive cushioning to boost their comfort and support, making the sneakers perfect for your infant's first steps. The scaled-down, timeless kicks subtly feature adidas's famous Three Stripes on the lateral and medial sidewalls. Also, the off-white leather mudguard improves the sneaker's durability, ensuring it suits your little one's physical activity levels.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Non-Reflective 2016

data.description: Taking on a unique colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga will add a hit of streetwear flair to any everyday look. Its breathable Primeknit upper boasts a marbled pattern as well as a vibrant orange sidewall stripe. Underfoot, the Boost midsole offers comfort and the semi-translucent outsole allows for effective grip. Fastened with an integrated lacing system, buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 Granite

data.description: Designed to bridge the gap between fashion and function, the adidas Yeezy 500 is one of Kanye West’s more abstract designs, and the Yeezy 500 Granite is an in-demand colourway. The upper is crafted from premium suede, while breathable mesh is added to allow air to flow freely around the foot to keep you cool. Set atop a contoured sole that’s built to support your foot in all the right places, expertly designed cushioning delivers industry-leading comfort and utility-style laces allow you to create a fit that feels practically customised. Easy to style thanks to the grey hue, the Yeezy 500 Granite is a must-have addition to your collection.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Mineral Blue

data.description: Dressed in a muted navy colourway, the Yeezy Foam Runner Mineral Blue promises to add futuristic flair to any everyday outfit. Its moulded EVA foam upper is complete with a series of holes which allow for effective ventilation. The textured outsole provides grip and the sculpted heel keeps your foot firmly in place all day long. Finished with minimal branding in true Yeezy fashion, the Yeezy Foam Runner Mineral Blue is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Mx Cream Clay

data.description: Another iconic offering in the form of a unique silhouette from Yeezy, the foam runner, now in an attractive colour palette of grey and cream for a refreshing, is a neutral look you can always depend on. Comfort, as always, is at the forefront of the Yeezy Foam Runner MX Cream Clay, making this sneaker perfect for runners and walkers alike. The shoe is made up of one piece of continuous foam ready to mould around your foot and provide maximum comfort with every wear. With this sleek design is a splattered cream and grey effect, which is unique, to say the least. This colour pattern continues onto the rubber sole of the Yeezy Foam Runner MX Cream Clay for maximum aesthetic design. The outer sole and overall design incorporates wavy lines and gaps for breathability, and the sole itself is built for maximum traction and support, as you would expect from a high-end runner.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 500 Soft Vision

data.description: Introduced in November 2019, the Yeezy 500 Soft Vision effortlessly fuses a highly technical design with fashion-focused details. Powered by a mesh, leather and suede construction, the tonal pink upper features functional laces and minimal branding. Underfoot, the sole houses adiPrene+ technology for all-day comfort and support. Buy and sell the Yeezy 500 Soft Vision with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 450 Sulfur

data.description: A sneaker that’s made to catch eyes, the Yeezy 450 Sulfur is a unique option that’s imbued with Ye’s - formerly known as Kanye West - signature style. The upper is crafted from a flexible knitted fabric that hugs your foot like a glove, while claw-like piping extends from the sole to the ankle to keep your foot firmly in place all day long. Utility-style laces are added so you can customise the fit, while the textured tread delivers enhanced grip. A must-have, wear the Yeezy 450 Sulfur with all your favourite outfits this season.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow

data.description: Fans of Yeezy will already be accustomed to the unique silhouette offering, and this pair of Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow sneakers is no different with its iconic shape. The Dark Glow version incorporates black, black, and more black — which is always a great look and one which is always going to stand the test of time for those fans of minimalistic and stylish options. The mesh panelling, sole, cage, and laces are all shown in black on the Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow. What’s great about this sneaker is that even though it’s entirely black, the subtle shade contrasting means you can see the individual panels, providing depth and layering to the overall look without it being too dark. Lighter black accents on the panels behind the cage offer a striped feature to this pair of Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow sneakers.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Pure

data.description: Crafted using environmentally conscious materials, the Yeezy Slide Pure is a minimalist option for off-duty days. The EVA Foam upper features a contoured footbed for comfort, while simple adidas branding is printed on the inside. A serrated sole ensures grip and the open toe allows air to flow around the foot to keep you cool. Buy and sell the Yeezy Slide Pure with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga 2.0

data.description: Paying homage to the OG Beluga 350, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga 2.0 presents an updated take on the classic Yeezy 350 model. Its breathable Primeknit upper is complete with contrasting SPLY-350 lettering, marbled detailing and a pull tab at the heel. The integrated lacing system allows for a secure fit, while Boost cushioning underfoot offers comfort. Rounded off with a rubber outsole for grip, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga 2.0 is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Mnvn Honey Flux

data.description: The latest addition to the expansive Yeezy catalogue, the Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Honey Flux arrives in a vibrant yellow hue across the nylon-crafted upper, offset by the model defining inverted branding that graces the lateral side panels joined by black flairs and reflective 3M accents on various areas. This loud, bold, and attention-grabbing cousin of the original Yeezy Boost 700 shape is certainly worthy of any sneakerheads rotation in 2022, and the Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Honey Flux is objectively one of the sharpest colourways on the market. Functionally the design is complete by a chunky midsole that's infused with adidas Boost cushioning technology for comfort, dipped in an all-black hue for a loud pop of contrast.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice

data.description: The Yeezy 350 has always been one of the most iconic Yeezy silhouettes to release. Ever since the first 'Turtledove' colourway, the 350 has become the go-to silhouette for many sneakerheads. The upcoming 'Mono' pack sees the dynamic duo of Adidas and 'Ye update the V2 350 with a Clay, Ice, and Mist colourway. All three silhouettes feature a translucent upper, revealing a web-like design underneath. In addition, the ever-present stripe across the sneaker's lateral side also features—the heel tab and infinity lacing system included complete the look of the upper. The instantly recognisable armoured sole unit features, with the now-famous Ultra Boost technology featuring. This renowned cushioning from Adidas means these Yeezy silhouettes are some of the most comfortable footwear on the market. The 'Mono' Pack is a welcomed fresh take on the classic Yeezy 350 V2 model, with all three colourways a must-cop for Summer.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Core

data.description: We see two brand new colourways of the Yeezy Slide release this week alongside a re-release of the Bone. The Yeezy Slide Core comes looking as if it was sculpted from clay. Although coming under some scrutiny when first released, the slide has since made a massive impact on the sneaker industry once people found out just how comfortable they were. The idea behind the silhouette was for wearing around the house or wherever you want to be cosy. This pair of Yeezy slide Core's is perfect for that. The Yeezy Slides Core colourway comes in Kanye's signature, subtle design dressed in a clay colour pallet. The natural hues ensure they are instantly recognisable as a Yeezy release. Crafted entirely from one piece of rubber to give the slide that futuristic look, something Kanye has strived for across many of his releases. The deep ridged sole which features is a nod towards the soles we are used to with the sneakers Yeezy releases. Branding is minimalistic, only featuring on the insole of the Yeezy Core With everybody working from home during lockdown, the Yeezy Slide Core is essential to be able to keep flexing whilst not leaving the house.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Mxt Moon Grey

data.description: Whether you're already a fan of Kanye West's Yeezy line, or if this is your first introduction, this pair of Yeezy Foam Runner MXT Moon Grey's isn't one to miss. The moon-grey colourway is one that's certainly an eye-catching one, offering a neutral scheme that feels as light and airy as the foam technology. The entirety of the Yeezy Foam Runner MXT Moon Grey's upper is created with caged-effect perforations for maximum breathability and versatility. The perforations range from small towards the front and middle of the sneaker, while they switch to larger towards the heel. The tan and grey tones combine for a stylish look, paired with the rubber sole that's built with boosted balance and comfort. The upper is complete with a series of ridges that will be familiar to any Yeezy fan.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 Bone White

data.description: Offering a pared-back take on the iconic silhouette, the Yeezy 500 Bone boasts a chunky frame and highly functional details. Crafted with suede and breathable mesh upper, it features a functional lacing system and suede overlays on the toe cap and sidewall. Complete with advanced cushioning underfoot, the Yeezy 500 Bone White is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 Mnvn Phosphor

data.description: The classic Yeezy silhouette gets an update, with the knitted and mesh upper now replaced with a comfortable and moulded nylon finish that’s built for lasting comfort and better weather protection. This striking Yeezy 700 MNVN Phosphor colourway comes complete with neon green-yellow along the top, paired with deep black on the eyelet panel, laces, and around the inside collar. The upper is then complemented by a strip of reflective silver in ‘700’ style and includes further reflective elements on the toe and on the heel. The usual Yeezy-boosted sole here comes in black rubber, with a firm grip and durability no matter the weather. The comfort and reflective technology of this Yeezy 700 MNVN Phosphor shoe means it’s the perfect choice for evening walks or runs to ensure that you’re seen.

fields.name: Yeezy Knit Rnr Stone Carbon

data.description: Designed with effortless functionality in mind, the Yeezy Knit RNR Stone Carbon is a sneaker, slip-on hybrid that delivers on versatility. The upper is crafted from a technical fabric that’s as durable as it is flexible, while a serrated outsole is added underfoot for grip. Minimalist adidas and Yeezy branding features on the collar, while lightweight cushioning underfoot makes for all-day comfort. Buy and sell the Yeezy Knit RNR Stone Carbon with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Mauve

data.description: Another example of the recognisable silhouette from Yeezy Boost, the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Mauve is a comfortable, understated shoe fit for purpose. The upper and sole are dominated by a deep shade of brown, with the darkest colour variation appearing on the suede overlays, which run along the side, toe, and eyelet panel. The fabric of the Yeezy 700 V2 Mauve is given a subtle reflective finish in deep hues of grey, which also appears on the laces. The chunky Boost-cushioned midsole incorporates a monochrome shade of mauve all the way along, while the outer sole embraces a lighter shade of brown. As with most Yeezys, the fit is on the smaller side, so make sure to take that into account when ordering your very own pair of Yeezy 700 Mauve sneakers.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Resin

data.description: The Yeezy Slide has become a staple for sneakerheads summer wardrobes, with the upcoming Yeezy Slide Resin colourway guaranteed to excite fans of both Yeezy and Adidas. The Yeezy Resin Slide perfectly fits with Kanye West's preferred aesthetics, with the earthy tone dominating the slide's design. Crafted from a single piece of EVA Foam, the comfort of the Yeezy Resin Slide is unbeatable and is what makes the slide such a must-have for collectors. The Yeezy Resin Slides are incredibly minimal in their design, with only a solo Yeezy logo featuring on the footbed. Releasing just in time for the warmer months, the Yeezy Slide Resin is a must cop for anybody looking to flex on the street and the beaches.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cmpct Slate Red

data.description: 2022’s take on Kanye West’s Yeezy Boost 350, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Red boasts the same streamlined style, but adds a higher collar for enhanced support. Much like the original, the upper on this iteration is crafted from a breathable, flexible knit fabric and utility-style laces are added so you can tighten or loosen the fit. A camo pattern adds just the right amount of detail, while adidas Boost cushioning underfoot delivers all-day comfort. Easy to style, let the bright red hue do all the talking by pairing the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Red with a pared-back outfit on off-duty days.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange

data.description: The Yeezy Slide is the beach-ready option from the Kanye West and Adidas collaboration, with the silhouette quickly becoming the must-have footwear for sneakerheads across the globe. The team are scheduled for one of the biggest releases of the Yeezy Slide we have ever seen, with five colourways dropping. We see the return of the Resin and Pure colourways, whilst 'Ye also adds Enfora Blue, Enflame Orange and Glow Green to the collection. The Yeezy Slide is known for its unbeatable comfort and minimalist aesthetics, thanks to the single piece of EVA Foam the silhouette is crafted from. You can find Adidas branding on the footbed of the slide, and that is all with minimalism key for the design of the slides. If you need a versatile piece of footwear, the Yeezy Slide is the perfect option.

fields.name: Yeezy Slides Bone

data.description: This week we were treated with the re-release of the Yeezy Slide Bone colourway, as well as two new colourways in Core and Soot. Although coming under some scrutiny when first released, the slide has since made a massive impact on the sneaker industry once people found out just how comfortable they were. The idea behind the silhouette was for wearing around the house or wherever you want to be cosy. This Yeezy slide is perfect for that. The light bone colourway is instantly recognisable as a Kanye creation as natural hues have become a mainstay for Yeezy releases. The futuristic look is down to the entire silhouette being crafted from once piece of rubber. The deep ridged sole is fitting when you look at the armoured style soles we are used to with Yeezy sneakers. Branding is minimalistic and can only be found on the insole. With everybody working from home during lockdown, the Yeezy Slide is essential to be able to keep flexing whilst not leaving the house.

fields.name: Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth

data.description: The unique Yeezy styling returns for a refreshingly blue and white offering in a futuristic styling for a comfortable and lightweight sneaker. The upper of the Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth comes with the breathable and supportive Flyknit sock backing, here shown in hues of royal blue, white and grey stitching running in stripes through. The grey features on the front and back of the shoe in a reflective thread. The fabric is then overlaid by a semi-translucent rubber caging with extra-large perforation detailing recognisable with the Yeezy styling. On top, a bold black is revealed for the collar as well as the laces. Clean white then features on the toe before moving into the curved rubber mid in seamless design. The outer sole then comes in white with grooved panels built for traction and support.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 High Utility Black

data.description: Borrowing design aspects from OG Yeezy 500 models, the monochrome Yeezy 500 High Utility Black showcases a boot-like update. Its ripstop mesh and suede upper features protective rubber mudguard panelling. Underfoot, adiPRENE+ cushioning in its midsole offers comfort and its rubber outsole provides effective grip on a range of terrains. Complete with internal padding and a secure lacing system, shop the Yeezy 500 High Utility Black with Laced now.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cmpct Slate Carbon

data.description: A fresh taken the iconic Yeezy Boost 350, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Carbon fuses Ye’s signature futuristic style with adidas’s industry-leading technology. The engineered knit upper hugs your foot like a glove, while an elastic cuff around the ankle further enhances the fit. Camouflage detailing throughout delivers extra style points, and the secure lace-up fastening is fitted with a toggle for quick and easy on-and-off. Underfoot, Boost cushioning offers support and comfort in equal measure, while grip comes courtesy of the textured tread. An effortless option for off-duty days, add the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Carbon to your collection now.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Mnvn Blue Tint

data.description: Boasting a futuristic design inspired by the Wave Runner, the Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Blue Tint puts comfort at the forefront of the silhouette. data.description: Kanye West is bringing back his Yeezy basketball silhouette just in time for the end of the NBA season. As Lebron James looks set to add another title to the trophy cabinet, you should most definitely be looking to add the Yeezy QNTM to your sneaker cabinet. The QNTM shoe was elevated to grail status when we saw Ye passing the sneaker out to passer's by at NBA all-star weekend in Chicago, back in February. The sneaker later saw a wider release and was an instant sell-out. This upcoming release is the second time we have seen an additional colourway of the highly sought-after basketball sneaker, following the release of the Barium earlier this year. The sneaker features a high-top design for additional ankle support, which has long been the norm for basketball silhouettes. A primeknit upper of course features, which we know offers comfort like no other. The uppers feature the classic neutral colour hues that Kanye loves to use, but with the addition of teal blue cross-stitched throughout to make the sneaker pop. Down below, a translucent midsole runs up the sides of each sneaker to give the shoe an incredibly futuristic yet sleek look. With the QNTM being one of Kanye West's more exclusive releases, we can guarantee the teal blue will be an instant classic. Be sure to add to your rotation today.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove

data.description: Being awarded the honour of being anointed 2015's ‘Shoe of the Year' at the Footwear News 29th Annual Achievement Awards, Kanye West has proven himself to be a designer at the forefront of trainer meta. First seen on Kanye and his models at the Yeezy Season 1 fashion show in February 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove was the second shoe released in the Adidas Yeezy collection after the Yeezy Boost 750 OG, and no one can argue its groundbreaking ethos and design features that debuted have changed the trainer landscape irreversibly. The t-shirt for your feet mantra that has been instilled through Kanye West's collaboration with Adidas is on display for all to see in this creation, and in many ways started the trend; soft Primeknit is utilised on the upper which showcases a gradient effect of black and off-white. A set of integrated rope laces are included, and a spiralled tubular sole sits underfoot. To complete the design, a subtle touch of red is stamped to the heel pull. This shoe is a piece of history, a trendsetter, a trailblazer, and everything that came after the Turtle Dove has it to thank for being the Yeezy equivalent of the first man on the moon.

fields.name: Yeezy 350 Oxford Tan

data.description: Released in 2015, the monochrome Yeezy 350 Oxford Tan is an OG colourway of the well-loved 350 model. Boasting a beige-toned design, its breathable Primeknit upper is complete with an integrated lacing system as well as a handy pull tab at its heel. Boost cushioning in the ridged midsole offers comfort, while the rubber outsole provides grip. Buy and sell the Yeezy 350 Oxford Tan with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Onyx Infants

data.description: Sporting a monochrome colourway, the slip-on Yeezy Foam Rubber Onyx Infants offers stylish versatility. Made from recycled foam, its upper features a series of cut-outs for ventilation as well as minimal branding. Underfoot, the soft footbed delivers comfort and the textured outsole provides all-important grip. Update your kid’s collection with the lightweight Yeezy Foam Rubber Onyx Infants.

fields.name: Yeezy Slides Bone Infant 2022

data.description: Tailoring the classic Yeezy Slide towards toddlers, the Yeezy Slides Bone Infants 2022 is crafted using lightweight EVA foam. Boasting a cream-toned colourway, the slip-on silhouette is detailed with minimal touches of branding. The soft footbed delivers comfort, the sawtooth outsole provides grip and the added heel strap offers extra support. Update your little one’s rotation with the Yeezy Slides Bone Infants 2022.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Pure Kids (2022)

data.description: Dressed in a minimal beige-toned colourway that will complement any of your little one’s looks, the Yeezy Slide Pure Kids (2022) is a slip-on staple for any starting collection. First released in 2021, this scaled-down slide was so sought-after that Ye decided to restock once again in 2022 to allow all kids to be able to experience the popular Yeezy design. Sporting understated adidas branding on the moulded footbed, its exaggerated ridged outsole ensures for all-important grip on any terrain. Its midsole is injected with EVA foam to craft this simple shoe with lightweight levels of comfort for everyday wear. The perfect no fuss kind of pair: the subtly stylish Yeezy Slide Pure Kids (2022) is an effortlessly easy option for those difficult days.

fields.name: Yeezy Slides Bone Kids 2022

data.description: The Yeezy Slides Bone Kids 2022 colourway proves kids are never too young to develop an effortlessly stylish wardrobe. The 2022 reissue of the classic slip-ons will delight most little ones, as it combines minimalistic style with exceptional comfort. The neutral colourway will allow your son or daughter to wear the shoes with most outfits they own, improving their fashion flexibility. They will feel as if they’re walking on a cloud, as each slip-on has injected EVA foam for a comfy, lightweight, and durable fit. It’s a perfect choice for spring or summer, as the open-toe design provides breathability, and the soft footbed will feel cosy on their feet when walking down the street or relaxing on the beach. The outsole has a sawtooth design for superb traction, grip, and impact protection.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay

data.description: With the release of the Yeezy Clay, Kanye West started the year as he means to go on with an already extensive array of products hitting shelves to further bolster his Yeezy catalogue in the opening months of 2019, and the March release of the Adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Clay is yet another excellent addition to an ever-evolving range. Sharing the same semi-translucent midfoot stripe which was debuted on this shoes Static cousin and with a paint job which could definitely be described as one of the most aesthetically pleasing to date, this kick in a lot of ways is an example of the progress Yeezy have achieved with one of their oldest models. The orange-tinted upper of the Yeezy 350 Clay sits atop a similarly coloured midsole which comes infused with the now legendary Boost technology to ensure levels of comfort run parallel with the standards of style, and we do not doubt that this new iteration is going to be another massive success for Ye.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Glow Green Kids 2021

data.description: Ye departed from his synonymous muted colour palette to release the vibrant Yeezy Slide Glow Green for kids of various ages in 2021. The bold and bright slides are unlike any other footwear design on the market for style and comfort. Rest assured, the colourful slides will feel cosy and lightweight, as they feature an injected EVA foam midsole. You can trust your kid will feel safe in the slides, as it has a rugged rubber outsole for improved traction and durability. In true Yeezy style, the Yeezy Slide Glow Green Kids 2021 slides aren’t dominated by branding, but you will find a debossed adidas logo on the footbed as a symbol of trust.

fields.name: Yeezy Desert Boot Rock

data.description: The Yeezy Desert Boot is one of Kanye West's first creations with Adidas, with the durable high top perfect for all terrains. 'Ye looks scheduled to drop two brand new colourways just in time for the Autumn months. The Yeezy Desert Boot 'Rock' colourway comes wholly covered in the light brown hue, with mesh, leather and suede all featuring. The Yeezy Desert boot is reminiscent of the Yeezy 500. This is thanks to the panelled design that runs across the lateral and medial sides of the boot. Thick rope laces complete the upper's appearance and ensure you can keep the shoes properly laced, whatever the weather. Underfoot the Yeezy Desert Boot Rock, a chunky sole unit with extreme traction featuring across the outsole guarantee unbeatable comfort wherever you wear your Yeezy desert boots.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Sand (Kids)

data.description: Your child will stand out from the crowd wearing the Yeezy Foam Runner Sand Kids colourway. The minimalistic aesthetic will add versatility to their stylish wardrobe, ensuring they look and feel effortlessly cool at the beach, on the street, or at the playground. The contemporary silhouette is super-comfortable, as it is built from a durable yet lightweight EVA foam, which is partially crafted from harvested algae. It features strategically mapped vents for exceptional airflow and breathability. If the above wasn’t enough, it has a sculpted heel with a soft footbed for a cosy yet secure fit. You will worry less about unwanted falls when your children are running or walking, as the clog-like shoes are finished with a hardwearing outsole that has a wavy traction pattern for exceptional grip.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue (Kids)

data.description: Let your kid run wild in style with the sleek Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue (Kids). With a slightly speckled black Primeknit upper and rope-inspired laces, this bold sneaker is a versatile classic with an added striking blue streak of personality across the side of the shoe. “SPLY-350” branding can be seen within the eye-catching stripe, nodding to the tailored construction of this well-loved silhouette and guaranteeing the ultimate fit for your little one. Complete with classic, grid-textured rubber outsole for optimum grip and full-length Boost midsole, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue (Kids) is the perfect balance between style and substance, making it the perfect addition to your kid’s growing collection.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2015)

data.description: Released in August 2015 the Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black has helped forge a path for one of the most hyped trainer lines in decades. Kanye West's collaboration with Adidas has seen breathtaking success since its inception at New York Fashion Week, and the Pirate Black has been one of the star players. This shoe featuring a black/grey Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole is slick and subtle. Oozing cool without making your eyes pop out your head this trainer appeals to fans of more understated fashion aesthetics, this piece is on trend and a must-have in any Yeezy Collection.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Reflective

data.description: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Reflective is a simple and subtle colourway from Kanye West’s iconic Yeezy Boost 350 V2 silhouette. Relying heavily on its ever-present blueprint to define its silhouette, the Citrin Reflective takes us back to the earthy tones, and subdued colours that formed the structural basis of the models early success. Featuring a cushioned sole unit appearing in a slightly translucent tan, it's complemented by the fan favourite gum tone. Both colours elevate the Primeknit upper — the shade of which is slightly greyed with small hints of an extremely light brown. Completing the look, striped detailing down the side provides contrast, balanced by hits of silver to bring the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Reflective Beige to a perfect close.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Mist Reflective

data.description: The Yeezy Boost range is no stranger to a futuristic silhouette and styling, and this pair of Yeezy Boost 380 Mist Reflective sneakers is no different. The upper reveals a crater-like extra-terrestrial pattern in flexible and lightweight Primeknit fabric, in soft neutral hues of beige, grey, and tan. The neutral colourway means a versatile shoe that can be worn anywhere, anytime, and will always look good. The threading design of the Yeezy Boost here again comes with the reflective qualities known to Yeezy to ensure you can remain seen. Alongside the prime knit upper, which completes with tan-brown laces and a grey collar trim, you then have a highly lifted sole, which comes complete with not only Boost technology for maximum comfort but a reflective rubber sheen throughout. The shoe is then finished with a deep brown rubber outer sole.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Vermillion Kids

data.description: Here in a stunning red vermillion hue in monochrome styling, the Yeezy Foam Runner Vermillion Kids arrives in smaller sizing so that your kids can enjoy this effortless style and comfort, too. Kanye West's iconic design here comes in a lightweight construction to make sure your kids' feet can remain ventilated for easy wear, built with EVA foam for a dependable design. This pair of Yeezys comes with everything you'd expect from this shoe range, including the clear perforated design with wide gaps and holes for extra breathability, as well as the easy slip-on style, which is perfect for kids on the go. The shoe also includes a rubber sole for extra support and traction for play or for relaxing. The bold red is a colour guaranteed to look good all year round.

fields.name: Yeezy Basketball Knit 3D Slate Blue

data.description: The Yeezy Basketball Knit 3D Slate Blue splices DNA from the Yeezy Quantum and the Yeezy 350 v2 silhouette to create a court lifestyle crossover featuring a Primeknit upper and signature Boost cushioning. Delivering a secure fit thanks in no small part to the sock-like construction previously adopted by some of adidas’ most iconic product lines but make no mistake, the experimental knit patterns, colour palette and sole unit are quintessentially Yeezy. The collaboration of grey with hints of blue that land at the tip of the forefoot and collar combine to create the titular “Slate Blue” arrangement, elevating this new school hardwood icon to an appropriately high level.

fields.name: Yeezy Slide Onyx Kids

data.description: Dropping in a nearly impossible-to-criticise black colourway, the Yeezy Slide Onyx Kids might just be the perfect sandal for your fashion-forward tots. Created entirely from rubberized foam the minimalist one-piece design is almost completely free from exterior branding, with only a Three-Stripe logo visible, imprinted in the soft top layer of the footbed almost as a subtle watermark proudly authenticating the latest addition to one of adidas’ proudest collaborative portfolios. Functionally, the Yeezy Slide Onyx Kids is finished with an Open-toe construction that delivers ever-present ventilated comfort, and an aggressive sawtooth outsole to give this design an aesthetic edge as well as a much-needed injection of both comfort and traction.

fields.name: Yeezy 350 V2 Earth

data.description: In neutral, deep, and rich earth tones, the Yeezy 350 v2 Earth is the ultimate in comfort, support, and style. While the sneaker maintains tones of deep khaki green and brown, the alternative textures and subtle colour changes make for an elegant design that is versatile enough for any outfit. The mesh side panelling in a deeper shade of brown breaks up the side panel of the Yeezy 350 v2 Earth, and the chunky khaki laces finish off the look. The knitted styling and silhouette are the iconic Kanye West design. The Yeezy 350 v2 Earth also includes a light brown back heel tab for effortless wear. As is common with the Yeezy fit, this sneaker is designed to be snug and supportive, so it’s recommended to go half a size up.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 High Mist Slate

data.description: Offering a boot-like take on the well-loved silhouette, the Yeezy 500 High Mist Slate comes dressed in a muted colourway. Its breathable neoprene base is layered with a mix of suede and leather panelling. Padding in the collar offers cushioning, the adiPrene midsole delivers comfort and the rubber outsole provides grip. Fastened with a secure lacing system, the Yeezy 500 High Mist Slate is available to buy and sell with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bred Infant
Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock

data.description: Following the success of the ‘Turtle Dove' and ‘Pirate Black' colourways, released in November 2015 the Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock first previewed on Instagram by Kim Kardashian is yet another excellent iteration in the constantly growing Yeezy catalogue. Sold exclusively at stores that carried Yeezy Season One Apparel, this release is as sought after as they come, and we can understand why. A Primeknit upper and ‘Moonrock' Boost outsole provide a delicate balance between comfort and style, that has become integral to the growing success of the Yeezy Boost 350. The Moonrock popularity is undoubtedly out of this world, so go on, treat yourself to a pair of Yeezy Trainers this year.

fields.name: Yeezy 350 V2 Yeezreel Reflective

data.description: The Yeezy 350 V2 Yeezreel Reflective bridges the gap between fashion and function. An eye-catching addition to Kanye West's expansive Yeezy 350 V2 catalogue is this particularly glowing variant of his idiosyncratic design. The traditionally observed sock-like Primeknit upper remains almost untouched, interwoven with a translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral and a rear pull tab with distinctive red stitching and bright rope laces to match. Underfoot a neon Tubular rubber sole reveals full-length energetic Boost technology, securing the status of this altogether iconic kick, full of substance as well as style.

fields.name: Yeezy Quantum Hires Coral

data.description: Released in 2022, the Yeezy Quantum silhouette makes a welcome return with a distinctive HiRes Coral colourway. The sneakers are anything but ordinary, offering a Primeknit build in a similar style to the popular Boost 350 V2 while featuring a curvy yellowed shell sidewall that adds texture and motion. Meanwhile, the teal-green collar, heel counter, tongue, and laces add depth and luxury, elevating your style. If a cool, modern colourway isn’t enough, you might be surprised to learn the Yeezy sneaker features impressive glow-in-the-dark elements. Also, the sneakers wouldn’t be complete without its signature Boost technology, providing superior comfort all day long.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Kids (Non-Reflective)

data.description: Following much demand to provide the whole family with a pair of matching Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneakers, Kanye West delivered this non-reflective black colourway. Released in 2019, the popular Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Kids Non-Reflective design features many elements from the original 350 V2 sneakers from 2016. For instance, it has a flexible Primeknit upper with integrated lacing, a translucent stripe along the lateral sidewall, and a handy heel loop. The innovative Boost cushioning creates a comfy, responsive fit, providing your child with more power when walking or running indoors or outdoors. The all-black upper is the epitome of stylish and contemporary and will help you develop a more versatile wardrobe for your child.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Stone Salt

data.description: Designed by Chicago-born rapper Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Stone Salt is one of the more futuristic styles to come out of the brand partnership. The upper is expertly crafted from a knit fabric that hugs the foot like a glove, while breathable perforations are added to ensure that air can flow freely. A secure lace-up fastening lets you customise the fit, while Boost cushioning underfoot provides comfort all day long. Rounded off with a textured tread for optimised grip, you can style the Yeezy Boost 380 Stone with absolutely anything and everything.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Teal Blue

data.description: Marking the ninth Yeezy 700 to drop in 2019. The Yeezy Boost 700 Teal Blue is like a hybrid between the ‘Wave Runner’ and the ‘Inertia’ colourways. Painted in various shades of blue, the upper is made of an ultra-breathable mesh for all-day wear, with leather and suede panels thrown across for the perfect balance. For a pop of contrast, a pair of bright orange laces add an option that is sure to turn heads wherever and whenever. As you move downwards, you’ll be greeted with an extra chunky foam midsole that’s painted in a complementary greyish blue hue. This houses one of Adidas’ thickest Boost units yet, and it’s all linked by a glorious gum rubber outsole that provides sneakerheads with extra comfort and durability.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia

data.description: The Inertia colourway for the Yeezy Boost 700 was regarded on release in early 2019, as one of the most attractive designs to brace the silhouette to date. The new Yeezy Boost 700 v2 Inertia symbolizes a redux of the colourway on their updated model. Maintaining the exaggerated proportions and intricate construction that has made both iterations so successful. This design softens the icon with a monochromatic mesh, suede and synthetic film upper. Leaning on the signature bluish-grey hues that made the Inertia such a popular colourway. Silver reflective accents settle on the heel. While a pop of colour hits the sculpted Boost midsole. That rides on top of a herringbone-patterned gum rubber outsole.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 High Mist Stone

data.description: It’s no secret that Chicago-born rapper Kanye West has a penchant for both boots and sneakers alike, so it makes sense that the adidas Yeezy 500 High Mist Stone is the perfect blend of both. A functional design with endless styling possibilities, this shoe uses premium fabrics, technical detailing and utility influences to cement it as a must-have in every collection. The upper is crafted from supple suede and a smooth scuba fabric, while the thick midsole is fitted with highly functional cushioning to deliver comfort and stability. The rope-style laces are rounded off with a toggle for quick fastening and the collar is padded for an extra element of comfort. Easy to wear thanks to its neutral colourway, add the Yeezy 500 High Grey Beige to your collection now and you’ll never want to take them off.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Kids)

data.description: If you're looking for something durable for your kid, this pair of minimalistic Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light Kids sneakers has it all. The breathable Primeknit upper reveals a creamy white texture for a colour that's going to suit almost any outfit and occasion. The knitted sock-like upper comes with clean white laces on top, as well as a semi-translucent peach-coloured pull tab at the heel. Comfortable Yeezy Boost technology is shown with the semi-translucent rubber midsole, which moves seamlessly into the rubber outer sole for a cohesive and stylish finish.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue Infants

data.description: A must-have addition to their everyday rotation, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue Infant is comfortable and stylish in equal measure. With all the details Yeezy 350s are famed for, the upper is crafted from a durable knit that hugs the foot like a glove. SPLY-350 is emblazoned across the side in a blue strip, while the utility-style laces up top are fitted with a toggle that makes them effortless to get on and off. Underfoot, adidas’s famous Boost cushioning keeps your little one comfy all day long, while the expertly crafted textured tread delivers grip for all their playtime adventures. Sure to be their new favourite pair, add the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue Infant to their collection now.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective

data.description: This pair of Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective sneakers provides the ultimate in a futuristic look, without going overboard, with its understated ‘peppered’ colourway and streamlined design. For fans of Yeezy, this is one highly anticipated release. The dependable sock-like fabric upper in timeless Yeezy design is crafted from Primeknit for the ultimate cosy fit. Here, it comes in fresh white with accents of light blue and pastel orange across the top. The whole upper is created for extra breathability and a lightweight design. The rubber sole of the Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective includes a white semi-translucent caging, behind which you can see the white Primeknit and the darker heel. The sole includes the must-have Boost technology for a balanced structure and a supported step for a comfortable wear every single time. White laces complete the clean upper.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Marsh

data.description: Set to release exclusively on Yeezy Supply and marking only the second 350 to drop since the turn of the decade, the sunflower shade Yeezy Boost 350 Marsh is understandable surrounded by much hype and speculation. Marking some newfound trends within the silhouette’s lexicon with soles marked with a middle stripe down its entire construction, breaking up the surrounding gum with a white accenting piece. Side stripes along the upper detail exist in the same fashion, even forgoing the patterns typically found on almost every prior release. The sunflower shade I previously referred to actually comes out as more of a dark mustard on the shoes interior and liner. One thing is for certain, although the Yeezy 350 is dropping colourways a lot more sparingly in 2020, the quality is still there with ever model.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Infants

data.description: Treat your little one to the versatile Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Infants, a smaller take on one of Kanye West’s most memorable models. Crafted from lightweight EVA foam for premium comfort, this neutral shoe will go with everything in your mini-me’s wardrobe. A streamlined, carved-out shape is what makes this recognisable shoe so iconic, made for optimal speed when it comes to running and reliable comfort for everyday wear. With open hole cut-outs for all-important grip and edgy Yeezy aesthetic, your kid will be the most stylish one in the playground with this beige-toned Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Infants.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Mnvn Bone Infant
Yeezy Foam Runner Mx Cream Clay Infants

data.description: The neutral Yeezy Foam Runner MX Cream Clay Infants design presents a versatile pair that your kid will love. The shoe is primarily cream with splashes of brown across, as well as accents of grey, along the upper. The lightweight EVA material allows for a comfortable wear and maximum durability. Its upper comes with the familiar design of flowing gaps and lines, as well as both wide and smaller holes, shown across the toe box and along the lower side panels wrapping around the shoe.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon Infants
Yeezy 450 Cinder Infants

data.description: Ensure your little one takes their first steps in style with the Yeezy 450 Cinder Infants. Sure to be their new favourite pair, this pair of Yeezys is crafted from an ultra-flexible knitted fabric that hugs their foot like a glove for comfort and security. The durable sole extends up the shoe to create a web, while a textured tread delivers grip. Up top, a toggle fastening makes getting the Yeezy 450 Cinder Infants off and on a breeze and the clean grey colourway will go with everything in their playtime wardrobe.

fields.name: Yeezy 500 Infant Stone Infant
Yeezy Boost V2 350 Beluga Reflective Infants

data.description: Ensure your kids can remain seen while enjoying the superior comfort of Yeezy with this pair of reflective Yeezy Boost V2 350 Beluga Reflective Infants. This infant styling of the popular adidas Yeezy Boost offers a minimalistic design with comfortable and breathable Primeknit for the upper. This is shown in a soft grey finish, paired perfectly with a neon coral orange side stripe, including SPLY-350 branding across. The breathable knit upper also includes reflective fibres throughout the upper, resulting in a hi-vis shoe that also reveals superior style. The Boosted midsole means a more cushioned and supportive step, perfect for those infants who see a lot of foot traffic while playing or adventuring, revealed in a semi-translucent light grey rubber finish for both the mid and outer sole. Deep grey laces on top finish the look.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya

data.description: When the Yeshaya colourway for the Yeezy Boost 350 v2 was first announced back in the Summer of 2019, it was expected to feature a never before seen colour palette that included purple yellow, and black. Well fast forward a few months and it appears Kanye West has stripped away the crazy, or maybe had a change of heart and what we are left with dropping in January 2020 is a colourway that is very much reminiscent of the previously released and very popular Static. All be it being made of a slightly darker Primeknit than previous designs. Black patterning introduces a pretty interesting look, while a mesh stripe shoots across the laterals.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue

data.description: Crafted with textural depth, the detailed Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue presents a detailed take on one of Kanye West’s most popular models. The layered mixed material upper includes premium swatches of suede, nubuck leather and smooth leather as well as breathable mesh sections. Dressed in understated tones of blue and grey, this intricate 700 iteration will complement any outfit, for any occasion. Underfoot, the signature chunky Boost midsole is accented with a pop of orange to add an eye-catching edge to this otherwise muted design. Finished with minimal branding in true Yeezy fashion, the modern Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue is an elevated essential for any collection.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream White (Infant)

data.description: Sporting an all-white colourway, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream White (Infant) will complement almost all of your little one’s looks. Its breathable Primeknit upper is complete with textured detailing and a handy pull tab at the heel. The integrated lacing system allows for a secure fit, while Boost cushioning offers comfort. Finished with a rubber outsole for grip, buy and sell the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream White (Infant) with Laced.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Kids

data.description: Following popular demand, adidas and Kanye West introduced a new collection of Wave Runner sneakers for kids. The contemporary Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Kids design has a mesh-woven base with layers of leather and suede materials for an elevated aesthetic and a comfortable fit. Your child can finally experience the comfort of a Boost midsole, as it provides responsive cushioning, exceptional comfort, and more power with every step. Completing the sneaker design is a black rubber outsole, which offers better grip and support as your child runs or walks. The stylish Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Kids shoe features the same black and grey colours from the original Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runners but includes contrasting accents, such as a blue toe box and orange dashes on the chunky midsole.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Non Reflective Infant
Yeezy Boost 700 Mnvn Orange

data.description: If you’re looking for a bright and bold head-turner, then nothing does it better than the iconic Yeezy silhouette coupled with neon orange. The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange is a pair of sneakers you won’t want to hide (and won’t be able to) with not only its bright orange upper but its silver reflective technology to ensure that you’re always seen. Black and orange work sleekly on this shoe for a rich, bold sneaker offering perfect for hot summer days and for runners, joggers, or walkers wanting to be seen day or night. The eye-catching orange upper includes silver reflective panels, and a chunky black sole includes the must-have cushioned Boost technology for stability and balance all day long. The Yeezy lacing system on the Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange is included in black, which looks fantastic against the offering of orange.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 750 Glow In The Dark

data.description: Shop the Yeezy Boost 750 Glow in the Dark today on Laced. Verified authentic on Europe’s largest sneaker marketplace.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Stone Sage Infants

data.description: Perfect for those get-up-and-go days, the Yeezy Foam Runner Stone Sage Infants promises to be their new favourite pair. Perfect for the warmer months, the upper is crafted from flexible, durable foam that’s specially contoured to fit perfectly without moving. Precisely placed cut-outs enhance air flow for comfort and breathability, while the versatile stone colourway means they’ll effortlessly pair with everything in their playtime rotation.

fields.name: Yeezy Desert Boot Oil

data.description: The Yeezy Desert Boot is one of Kanye West's first creations with Adidas, with the durable high top perfect for all terrains. 'Ye looks scheduled to drop two brand new colourways just in time for the Autumn months. The 'Oil' colourway features a stealthy black hue throughout the design. Mesh, leather and suede all feature across the upper, giving the shoe a seriously luxurious look. The panelled design you find across both lateral and medial sides of the boot draws clear inspiration from one of Kanye West's other creations, the Yeezy 500. Thick rope laces complete the upper's appearance and ensure you can keep the shoes properly laced, whatever the weather. Underfoot, a chunky sole unit with extreme traction featuring across the outsole guarantee unbeatable comfort wherever you wear your Yeezy desert boots.

fields.name: Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Kids

data.description: Sporting a yellow-toned colourway, the Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Kids is perfect for easy everyday styling. Made from lightweight EVA foam, its upper features a series of cut-outs for effective ventilation. The soft footbed offers comfort and is detailed with minimal branding, while the textured outsole provides grip. Refresh your little one’s rotation with the slip-on Yeezy Foam Runner Sulfur Kids.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bred Kids

data.description: Ensure your little one steps out in style with the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bred Kids. Perfect for the days you want to go matching, this miniature Yeezy takes after the adult version with its knitted upper, Boost cushioning and utility-style laces. One of the most iconic silhouettes to come out of the adidas x Kanye West collaboration, the 350 dons Ye’s signature futuristic look while keeping the aesthetic pared-back enough to wear on the daily. So good your kids will never want to take them off, add the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bred Juniors to their collection now.

fields.name: Yeezy Knit Rnr Fade Indigo

data.description: The minimalist Yeezy Knit RNR Fade Indigo is the ultimate slip-on. Offering a sock-like aesthetic and a gradient knitted upper, the shoes will feel soft, comfortable, and responsive on your feet. The ombre effect provides pops of blue, green, and indigo, which help to elevate the premium design further. A pair of the Yeezy Knit Runners will feel as light as a feather on your feet, as the cosy midsole unit is infused with a hidden EVA foam for lightweight cushioning. You will hardly know you're wearing the cool, cloud-like design. Of course, as you would expect from Kanye West, the stretchy slip-on sneakers feature minimal branding, apart from the classic adidas logo on the brown rubber outsole, which includes a modified herringbone tread for excellent grip and traction.

fields.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids

data.description: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is one of the brand's most comfortable silhouettes. The cosy fit is due to the Primeknit upper and full-length Boost technology sole unit, which will make your kid feel as if they're walking on a cloud. data.description: The Yeezy Foam Runner Ararat debuted at London Fashion Week 2020 to much acclaim and launched in June of the same year via Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply site. The distinctive colourway is inspired by Kim Kardashian’s Armenian heritage and named after Mount Ararat, a volcanic mountain found in the Armenian Highlands that is believed to be the home of Noah’s Ark. At first glance, you might question how the shoe relates to the mountain, but the white aesthetic is inspired by the snow-caps of Ararat. The execution is just as interesting as the slip-on’s history, as it is created from a unique foam compound that combines harvested algae with a lightweight EVA. As a result, the Yeezy Foam runners will feel comfortable and lightweight each time you slide them onto your feet. The monochromatic colourway and sculpted lines create a futuristic aesthetic while complementing many everyday looks. The oval cut-outs across the upper boost airflow, making the slip-ons ideal for the beach or street.

data.description: After legendary collaborations with sportswear giants Nike and Asics, Round Two founder Sean Wotherspoon is back again this time pairing up with Adidas. This project indicates the first time Wotherspoon has worked with Adidas, but if his previous collabs are anything to go by, these are going to be an instant classic. The sneaker Wotherspoon has added his touch of magic to is none other than the cult classic Superstar. A shoe made famous by Run DMC many years ago is now celebrating its 50 anniversary, so it made perfect sense for Sean to add the Round Two vibe to this silhouette. The theme behind the sneaker is sustainability, which makes perfect sense with Wotherspoon being a proud vegan. The shoe will be made with vegan-friendly products and constructed of upcycled fabrics. The shoe features multi-coloured flowers stitched across each side. This vibrant colour scheme is something that we now expect with the designer's work. A slightly stranger aspect of the shoe is the paper laces included. The iconic shell-toe of course features, whilst the sole remains white rubber to ensure the sneaker still looks and feels like a superstar. A cork insole, composite padding and a sock liner crafted from waste rubber rounds of this sustainable take on a classic. If you want to want to stand out from the crowd, then look no further than Wotherspoon's latest masterpiece.
