Hues from both Michael Jordans college and pro teams are represented via powder blue elements from the University of North Carolina Tar Heels, and gym red touches extracted directly from the Chicago Bulls. Finishing the look are toe box perforations and a rubber outsole with a pivot point tread pattern.

fields.name: A Ma Maniere X Air Jordan 1 Burgundy Sail

data.description: The latest sneaker to come out of the A Ma Maniere x Jordan Brand collaboration, the A Ma Maniere x Air Jordan 1 Burgundy Sail is the definition of luxe. Paying respect to the original AJ1 design, AMA has kept the shoe pared-back and elegant, holding back on embellishments to add a premium spin to the silhouette. The upper comes in plush suede with the Swoosh and ankle arriving in faux snakeskin to add textural depth to the design. Breathable perforations sit on the toe box, while Jordan’s Wings logo adorns the ankle in the same rich burgundy hue as the laces and branding. Underfoot, just the right amount of cushioning is added to ensure comfort and stability when you wear the coveted A Ma Maniere x Jordan 1.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low X Eastside Golf Midnight Navy

data.description: The Jordan Brand has partnered with Eastside Golf, an Atlanta-based golf brand, to put fresh twists on its classic Air Jordan 1 silhouette. The duo has teamed up to breathe new life into golf attire, which is why they dropped the stylish Midnight Navy colourway in 2022. The deep blue nubuck upper gives the timeless AF1 a more premium feel and is complemented by luxurious Metallic Gold lace tips that will increase your style confidence on the golf course or street. Completing the design is a Redstone outsole to represent the red clay mud you might land in following a poor swing and is featured to remind you that you can overcome any adversity you face on a course. As a seal of approval, you'll find the Eastside Golf logo on the heel and a special edition hangtag, which complements the black medial and lateral Nike Swooshes, insole Jumpman, and wings motif on the tongue.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low Lv8D Silver Toe Womens

The LV8D iteration sticks to Air Jordan 1’s classic colour-blocking theme but gives the sneakers a unique spin. The stylish design is sure to stand out in any crowd, offering an almost sparkly metallic toe, heel tab, and heel counter, giving the silhouette character and texture. The shiny elements are balanced by clean white quarters that contrast with a jet-black overlay, laces, tongue, and Nike Swooshes on the lateral and medial sidewalls. The chunky white platform sole elevates the design and provides more room for foam cushioning for extra comfort. You can enjoy superior cushioning with each step you take, thanks to the encapsulated Air-Sole unit at the heel.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Inside Out Black

data.description: The Air Jordan 1 continues its love affair with deconstructed designs, which are delighting sneaker fans worldwide. After clasping your eyes on the mid-top Inside Out Black colourway, it's easy to see why the theme is becoming increasingly popular. The stylish sneaker has a flipped construction, providing an insight into details usually invisible in the design, such as an exposed foam tongue and collar, underlying panels, and contrast stitching. Some details have been rearranged on the design, as the perforated toe box forms part of the overlay, and the heel tab is lower than usual for the mid-top AF1. The simple lateral and medial Nike Swooshes manage to stand out due to the exposed stitching and a pop of orange.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low Grey Red

Boasting a premium fabrics and a durable build, the upper is crafted from a blend of leather and suede for a modern multi-textured look. The toe box is detailed with breathable perforations, while Swoosh and Jordan branding can be found on the heel and sidewalls. Of course, no Jordan would be complete without Michael Jordan’s Jumpman and this AJ1 Low has the motif stitched onto the tongue. Easy to style thanks to the clean grey, white and red finish, the Air Jordan 1 Low Grey Red is one of those pairs that you’ll want to wear on repeat.

fields.name: Air Jordan 5 Aqua

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Se Utility Womens

The sidewalls are finished with Swoosh logos and the tongue comes complete with Michael Jordan’s Jumpman logo. Underfoot, Air cushioning ensures comfort and bounce both on and off the court, while the textured tread delivers grip. Easy to style thanks to the black, white and red colourway, the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Utility Black White is an absolute must-have.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Grey Onyx Womens

data.description: Make a style statement with a pair of Air Jordan 1 Mid Grey Onyx Women's sneakers. The simple yet sleek shoes feature two attractive grey tones to complement many clothes hanging in your wardrobe. Standing out against the light upper and dark grey overlays are the tan Nike Swooshes on the medial and lateral sidewalls. The supportive mid-top sneaker features the iconic Jumpman on the tongue tab and the synonymous Wings adorn the ankle strap. A chunky white midsole finishes off the neutral design, adding a burst of freshness to ensure the shoe suits every season. Thanks to the padded ankle support, perforated toe box, and signature cushioning, you can trust the sneakers will feel supportive, breathable, and comfortable on your feet. The Air Jordan 1 Mid Grey Onyx Women's is a classic yet modern sneaker you'll be proud to wear throughout the years.

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Low Coconut Milk

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Grey Blue Womens

fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Turf Orange Gs

data.description: If you're a basketball and Air Jordan fan, then bold and bright orange is a colour you'll be familiar with, and the Air Jordan 1 Mid Turf Orange GS sneaker takes advantage of this attractive neon shade. fields.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Triple Black

data.description: Introducing the ASICS Gel-Lyte III OG Backstreets of Japan Ivory. It is a homage to the sneaker’s roots, as the silhouette was designed by Shigeyuki Mitsu, a Japanese footwear designer, in 1990. For this reason, the neutral shoe’s colour palette aims to mirror Japan’s energetic atmosphere at night. The cool kicks retain the original shape and construction from the 1990s and include the popular GEL-Lyte 3 split tongue design. The sleek sneakers feature an ivory and grey mesh and suede upper, contrasting with jet-black laces and splashes of mint green. The quarter and heel webbing provides an extra layer of texture and contrast with the black leather ASICS branding in black. All-day comfort is expected due to the popular GEL cushioning technology unit inside the white midsole.

Underfoot, N-ergy cushioning is expertly designed to support your foot in all the right places and the toothy-textured tread gives that “Dad-shoe” look NB is famed for. The rest of the shoe continues the timeless white, with a white rubber midsole, grooved rubber outer sole and white laces, along with a white fabric collar and fabric tongue. Adhering to that same design update, the Joe Freshgoods version takes the design even further with ‘Outside Clothes’ stitching and a logo-emblazoned tag swinging from the laces. Underfoot, the shoe’s original 1989 running technology remains unchanged, giving the wearer that same comfort and performance, and the New Balance ’N’ on the side of the shoe also nods to its nostalgic roots. One of the brand’s more tough-to-get sneakers, grab the Joe Freshgoods x New Balance 990v3 Outside Clothes while it’s in stock!

This switches to a bright golden yellow leather panelling along the main bulk of the upper, with gaps revealing a perforated white backing panel across the toe and side fronts. White is repeated for the smooth leather panels around the collar of the sneaker, while bold black laces help the colours to stand out. For the sole, you have a textured white and grey finish along the chunky midsole, with a reflective strip to the back and a black rubber outer sole to finish.

Complete with crisp white laces and a branded tongue label to match, the delicate New Balance 327 Morning Fog Women’s is the pastel refreshment that your collection craves.

data.description: In 2001, functional footwear brand New Balance launched the NB991, then five years later, the slightly updated NB992 landed on shelves and quickly because a favourite for athletes, fashion insiders and - ahem - Steve Jobs. The upper boasts a supple suede fabrication and the underlay is made of breathable mesh that pushes air around the foot to keep you cool. New Balance’s instantly recognisable ’N’ logo sits on the sidewalls and reflective panels are added so you can be seen in low-light conditions. Presented in an ultra-wearable ivory and grey finish, the New Balance 992 Nimbus Cloud White offers endless styling options.

fields.name: New Balance 550 White Cool Grey

data.description: The minimalist New Balance 550 White Cool Grey will allow you to create an effortlessly stylish, versatile wardrobe. The simple yet effective iteration will match many everyday outfits, including a simple pair of jeans, a pair of shorts, or jogging pants. The perforated white leather upper adds texture while improving breathability, and the cool grey heel counter, collar, and midsole help to create a more sophisticated aesthetic.
